result.formatted_address: 3/F California Tower, 30-32 D'Aguilar St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Beef & Liberty Burgers Lan Kwai Fong

reviews.text: I've to say that is the first time in my life I order a burger and it doesn't come with French fries that have to be ordered separately, the plate looked so empty even for the small size of the burger. The meat cooking was more raw then medium. I also felt something wrong with the French fries, may be the oil has been used too much anyway their quality was not high. Overall flavour of the burger was just the taste that a burger would have with just a little bit of cheese and some beacon, something was missing. The environment and design is good.

Great atmosphere and friendly staff! So much potential.
The burgers and fries were average 😕
I was expecting large western style burgers, but they were just regular small HK style burgers. Plastic tasting buns and undercooked meat. Disappointed that I had to order the fries separately. They don't come with the burger? Odd...
Chilly cheese fries were bland and nothing like the classic American kind. For over $60 I would expect better fries.
Unfortunately, I won't be coming here again. Not worth the travel or cost.

The service here is always amazingly friendly and I've never had food. I really like the ambiance of the place. The lighting is good and the layout is nice. It feels lively but never crowded or awkward. And kudos for offering bunless burgers and a nice selection of craft beers.

Great atmosphere cause it’s not too loud that you can’t hear the people you’re with. Staff were nice and very attentive. Food is delicious (a little overpriced but that’s the area). They also have happy hour :)

First it was hard to find. You pay $20 bucks for 1 burger and empty space on the plate. I asked for a cooked burger and got a raw one. It took 20 mins to get a new one. I wouldn’t recommend this place. It’s fancy inside but it seems that’s what you are paying for.

result.adr_address: 30-32 D'Aguilar St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: California Tower

reviews.text: Big tower. Good views on a clear night. Quite expensive but you’d expect that at the top!
Gorgeous rooftop bar, Ce La Vie on the very top floor! Beautiful views of Hong Kong.

Good selection of restaurants from the bottom floor to the top. Or if you want to get your sweat on then I'd highly recommend signing up for the Pure gym - chances are this is the closest one to those working in central. Top floors have pretty great views, particularly towards the south.
There's this bar located at the rooftop called Cest La Vie. A really nice bar to chill at! Love it!
Pure Fitness at California tower is the best gym in town!
